  "prompt": "What does \"dying from exposure\" mean?",
  "response": "\"Dying from exposure\" refers to a situation in which a person succumbs to the effects of extreme environmental conditions, particularly cold weather, but it can also apply to excessive heat or other harsh conditions. In the context of cold weather, it typically means that a person has been subjected to low temperatures for an extended period without adequate protection, leading to hypothermia or frostbite, which can ultimately result in death. In hotter conditions, it can refer to heat exhaustion or heat stroke from prolonged exposure to excessive heat. The term emphasizes the dangers of the elements and the body's vulnerability to them without proper shelter or protection.",
